	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">pemdawg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Would this be possible? If the two games are unchanged beyond the game select menu, couldn't one feasibly insert data for different NROM games into it?</div>That's possible, but doesn't really save you much. You'll still need to both draw new menu items and modify the games to return control to the menu on power-up (The version of SMB in this multicart 'MHROM' differs in the 2nd through 9th bytes from the non-multicart version)â€”otherwise the SMB-replacement stands a 50% chance of running instead of the menu. You might consider starting with something like mapper 41 (Caltron 6-in-1) instead.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
